The paper deals with the problem of identifying figurative language in short texts, which is a subfield of Natural Language Processing (NLP). The use of advanced Deep Learning (DL) methodologies and neural network architecture is also mentioned, which suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Machine Learning (cs.LG, cs.NE). Additionally, the use of social media discussion forums and chats as a source of data suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of Cybersecurity (cs.CY).
